11/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- A blaze fuelled by high winds threatened the town of Seferihisar in the western province of Izmir on Monday (August 10th), burning about 600 hectares of forests and 100 hectares of arable land.
About 300 fire-fighters supported by special vehicles and aircraft managed to get the flames under control early Tuesday.
Hundreds of houses and summer villas in the area were evacuated.
(Milliyet, Anadolu news agency, BTA - 11/08/09)
